text: Barbara Joyce Dainton (née West; May 24, 1911 – October 16, 2007) was the second-to-last remaining survivor of the sinking of the RMS Titanic. She was the last living survivor who had travelled under second class on the ship. West was born in Bournemouth, England. She died at age 96 in Truro, Cornwall.
